      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.unJ8E4IikZUxT7x3]{Temporal Anomalies (Su)}</p>\n<p>You can trap others in a moment, leaving them frozen in time. Once per day as a full action, you can force a creature within 60 feet of you to pause, freezing them in time. The creature must succeed at a Will saving throw or gain the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.NV4qXRDgb7zTNkW2]{Paralyzed} condition for a number of rounds equal to your Dexterity modifier. Each round, that creature can retry this saving throw as a full action; if they succeed, they break free and re-enter the timestream, and the temporal backlash deals you 10 damage per round that the target was paralyzed. This damage canâ€™t be reduced in any way.</p>"
